title: Ukulele Club returns to library
text:
Ukulele Club returns to library Oct 24, 2015 Celia Jones is pictured with a student during a Rockland Public Library uke event. 
Rockland — Rockland Public Library, 80 Union St., offers another drop-in Ukulele Club for all ages and skills Mondays, Nov. 2 and 16, from 5:30 to 6:30 p.m. 
The events, hosted by music teacher Celia Jones, will take place in the downstairs Friends Community Room and is open to ukulele devotees of all ages. Some ukes will be provided or people can bring their own. 
Ukulele Club is part of The Arts … for Kids and their Families series. For more information, contact Rockland Public Library at 594-0310. 
Courier Publications’ A&E Editor Dagney C. Ernest can be reached at (207) 594-4401, ext. 115; or dernest@courierpublicationsllc.com.
